# Edge redirects for Cloudflare Workers Assets (processed by the asset layer,
# before the Worker, exactly like the sibling _headers file).
#
# RETIRE THE OLD APP: send every visitor — browser AND installed PWA — from the
# old app's entry routes to the rebuilt v2 SPA. The old entry pages, their
# client-side standalone-only redirect, and all the old orchestrator modules are
# left in place UNCHANGED as a one-step rollback: delete this file and the old
# app serves again (browsers get it directly; the PWA's own standalone redirect
# still bounces it to /v2/). 302 (temporary) so nothing caches the redirect hard
# while the rollback window is open.
#
# Only the exact navigation routes are matched — never the shared assets under
# /macro/js, /credit/js, /legal/js, /premium.css, … which v2 still loads — so a
# wildcard must never be used here. Deep links into a desk are hash-based
# (/credit/#fund/x); the browser re-appends the fragment to the redirect target,
# and the v2 apps preserve hash sub-routing, so those links keep working.

/                    /v2/           302
/index.html          /v2/           302
/macro               /v2/macro/     302
/macro/              /v2/macro/     302
/macro/index.html    /v2/macro/     302
/credit              /v2/credit/    302
/credit/             /v2/credit/    302
/credit/index.html   /v2/credit/    302
/legal               /v2/legal/     302
/legal/              /v2/legal/     302
/legal/index.html    /v2/legal/     302
/menu                /v2/menu/      302
/menu/               /v2/menu/      302
/menu/index.html     /v2/menu/      302
